<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1333,1999]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
1 Pronotum slender; its surface quite smooth and tubercles indistinct; prozona very low, its lobes indistinct; metazona long (
<quantity box="[396,496,1373,1399]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4097" metricValueMax="1.5493999999999999" metricValueMin="1.27" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="in" value="5.55" valueMax="6.1" valueMin="5.0">5–6.1 in</quantity>
male; 
<quantity box="[586,665,1373,1399]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.651" metricValueMax="1.778" metricValueMin="1.524" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="in" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 in</quantity>
female) and narrow; lateral projections of mesozona indistinct (Figs. 4a, b, c, d); female with smallest size in the species (
<quantity box="[880,1034,1413,1439]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.94" metricValueMax="3.18" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="29.4" valueMax="31.8" valueMin="27.0">27–31.8 mm</quantity>
); hind tibia dark blue in basal part, apical 1/4 turns to red; male tegmina reaching beyond hind knee (Figs. 4a, c); found from Bozkır and environments (
<figureCitation box="[374,451,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1523,1547]" captionTargetBox="[342,1244,195,1495]" captionTargetId="figure-153@32.[332,1254,194,1500]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Distributions of the taxa. 15, distributions of the species; 16, distributions of the subspecies of G. holtzi and the determined contact zones; 17, distributions of the subspecies of G. escherichi and G. dimorphus and the determined contact zones." pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig.16</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[461,1285,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">................................................................................................... turcicus</emphasis>
Ünal, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1364,1433,1493,1519]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="subSpecies">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1364,1426,1493,1519]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">ssp.n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1333,1999]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
- Pronotum stout with distinct tubercles (except some individuals of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Uvarov" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[985,1214,1533,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="holtzi" subSpecies="pulchripes">
<emphasis box="[985,1214,1533,1558]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">G. holtzi pulchripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); prozona high, its lobes distinct; metazona shorter (
<quantity box="[585,683,1573,1599]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1938" metricValueMax="1.3716" metricValueMin="1.016" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="in" value="4.7" valueMax="5.4" valueMin="4.0">4–5.4 in</quantity>
male; 
<quantity box="[762,881,1573,1599]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4478" metricValueMax="1.7018" metricValueMin="1.1938" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="in" value="5.7" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="4.7">4.7–6.7 in</quantity>
female) and broad; lateral projections of mesozona very distinct (
<figureCitation box="[423,536,1613,1639]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionStartId-1="13.[151,255,1434,1458]" captionTargetBox-0="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetBox-1="[155,1420,567,1404]" captionTargetId-0="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetId-1="figure-400@13.[140,1446,554,1410]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="13" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 3. Glyphotmethis holtzi holtzi, FIGURE 4. Glyphotmethis holtzi turcicus ssp.n.: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
: a, b, c, d); female with larger size (
<quantity box="[954,1083,1613,1639]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="33.0" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="30.0">30–36 mm</quantity>
) ........................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1333,1999]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<materialsCitation country="Turkey" location="Unal" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" specimenCount="2" specimenCount-male="2">
<specimenCount box="[151,258,1653,1679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="male">2 Male</specimenCount>
tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[376,498,1653,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="10.[151,255,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[154,1400,845,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-408@10.[140,1446,837,1693]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 1. Glyphotmethis holtzi brachypterus ssp.n., FIGURE 2. Glyphotmethis holtzi pulchripes: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs. 1a, c</figureCitation>
) distinctly shortened, shorter than 
<quantity box="[903,989,1653,1679]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
, reaching at most tohalf of hind femur or in well prepared specimens reaching to 5th–6th abdominal tergites;metazona short and broad, 1.5 times broader than long in male; hind tibia dark blue in basal part, apical 1/3 turns to red; found from 
<locationDeviation location="Central" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">W of Central</locationDeviation>
<collectingCountry box="[245,346,1773,1799]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[362,447,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1523,1547]" captionTargetBox="[342,1244,195,1495]" captionTargetId="figure-153@32.[332,1254,194,1500]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Distributions of the taxa. 15, distributions of the species; 16, distributions of the subspecies of G. holtzi and the determined contact zones; 17, distributions of the subspecies of G. escherichi and G. dimorphus and the determined contact zones." pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[461,1285,1773,1798]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">...........................................................................................brachypterus</emphasis>
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:FC74BA0DFFF7E634FF5749825397FE0C:71025DC0FFF7E63BFACC4B85534AF8A9" box="[1292,1351,1773,1799]" country="Turkey" name="Unal" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ünal</location>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1364,1428,1773,1799]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="subSpecies">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1364,1428,1773,1799]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">ssp.n</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</materialsCitation>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1428,1434,1773,1799]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">.</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1333,1999]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
- Male tegmina (Figs. 2–3: a, c) long, longer than 
<quantity box="[765,851,1813,1839]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
, reaching at least to genicular lobes of hind femur or in well prepared specimens reaching to genital region of abdomen (mostly reaching to hind knee and beyond it); metazona 1.4 times broader than long in male.......................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1333,1999]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,152,418]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
3 Lateral margins of metazona concave (Fig. 2a); male tegmina narrow (
<quantity box="[1059,1187,1933,1959]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="4.1" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.2">3.2–5 mm</quantity>
); reaching mostly to hind knee in typical forms (Figs. 2a, c), in some others reaching to genicular lobes of hind femur or just beyond hind knee; inner side of hind tibia predominantly dark blue in basal 1/2–3/4 part, apical part turns to red or orange-red, in some specimens fully black, dark blue or violet; known from middle part of Central 
<collectingCountry box="[245,346,232,258]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[362,447,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1523,1547]" captionTargetBox="[342,1244,195,1495]" captionTargetId="figure-153@32.[332,1254,194,1500]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Distributions of the taxa. 15, distributions of the species; 16, distributions of the subspecies of G. holtzi and the determined contact zones; 17, distributions of the subspecies of G. escherichi and G. dimorphus and the determined contact zones." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[461,1199,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">....................................................................................................</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Uvarov)" baseAuthorityName="Uvarov" box="[1200,1433,232,258]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Asiotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchripes">
<emphasis box="[1200,1319,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">pulchripes</emphasis>
(Uvarov)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,152,418]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
- Lateral margins of metazona straight (
<figureCitation box="[666,755,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,255,1434,1458]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,567,1404]" captionTargetId="figure-400@13.[140,1446,554,1410]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Glyphotmethis holtzi holtzi, FIGURE 4. Glyphotmethis holtzi turcicus ssp.n.: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
); male tegmina broad (
<quantity box="[1042,1191,272,298]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="4.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="5.3" valueMax="5.7" valueMin="4.9">4.9–5.7 mm</quantity>
) and long, reaching always to hind knee or beyond it (
<figureCitation box="[614,742,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,255,1434,1458]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,567,1404]" captionTargetId="figure-400@13.[140,1446,554,1410]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Glyphotmethis holtzi holtzi, FIGURE 4. Glyphotmethis holtzi turcicus ssp.n.: a, male pronotum, tegmina and hind wing from above; b, female pronotum and tegmina from above; c, male pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; d, female pronotum and tegmen, lateral view; e, male lateral view; f, female lateral view; g, apical valves of penis and cingulum, lateral view; h, ditto posterior view; i, epiphallus. Scales 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs. 3a, c</figureCitation>
); inner side of hind tibia dark red or bluish-red in typical forms, in some other specimens basal part dark blue, apical 1/3 part turns to red as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Uvarov" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[1200,1428,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="holtzi" subSpecies="pulchripes">
<emphasis box="[1200,1428,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">G. holtzi pulchripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; known from SE of Central 
<collectingCountry box="[517,618,392,418]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[634,719,392,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="32.[151,269,1523,1547]" captionTargetBox="[342,1244,195,1495]" captionTargetId="figure-153@32.[332,1254,194,1500]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Distributions of the taxa. 15, distributions of the species; 16, distributions of the subspecies of G. holtzi and the determined contact zones; 17, distributions of the subspecies of G. escherichi and G. dimorphus and the determined contact zones." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[732,1252,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">.......................................................................</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Werner)" baseAuthorityName="Werner" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1256,1434,392,418]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glyphotmethis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holtzi">
<emphasis box="[1256,1321,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holtzi</emphasis>
(Werner)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
